headline.main: AUCHINLECK TRICK IS FEARED BY ITALY; Rome Is Not So Sure British Will Be Pushed Out of Egypt in Sudden Defeat SYRIA MOVE IS WATCHED Axis Troops Poised in Greece and Rhodes Might Be Used to Divert Defense

lead_paragraph: BERNE, Switzerland, June 30 -There is an incongruous note of cautious hesitation apparent in today's Italian press, which plays the story of the Axis armies' continued successes on the North African front under banner headlines, but in editorial comment warns the reader that "although the Egyptian battle is now entering its decisive phase with the initiative in our hands, there are still several questions to be answered."
